Recommended next steps (exact code change to make)
You have two sensible options. Pick one.

Option A — Add the expected fields to User (recommended quick fix)
- Modify src/main/java/com/java_template/application/entity/user/version_1/User.java to include plaintext/demo fields that the criteria refer to:

Add these fields to the User class (inside the class body, alongside other fields):
  private String password;     // plaintext for validation in demo only
  private String externalId;   // optional external identifier

Because Lombok @Data is already present, adding these fields will generate getPassword() and getExternalId() automatically and resolve the compile errors.

Example patch (replace the User class fields block or insert lines):
  // existing fields
  private String passwordHash; // hashed password
  // ADD:
  private String password; // plaintext for validation in demo only
  private String externalId;

You may want to adjust isValid() to consider password or leave it as-is (depending on business logic). For demo/compile purposes, adding the fields is enough.

Option B — Change the criteria to use existing User fields
- Update ValidateUserCriterion to check user.getPasswordHash() (and/or adjust to read a separate extras class), and update DuplicateUserExistsCriterion to check an existing user field (if one exists), or use a different mechanism that matches the User implementation.
- This is more invasive to business logic; Option A is simpler for compilation.

Why I recommend Option A
- The criterion code explicitly expects getPassword() and getExternalId(); adding these fields to User is minimally invasive and matches the intent of the criteria (they validate a plaintext password length and check externalId presence).
- It is quick and will fix the remaining compile errors without touching many other files.

